## Content Patterns

This template showcases several content authoring patterns. Explore these files to understand how they work.

### Content Collections

Collections turn folders of markdown files into queryable data. Each file has frontmatter (metadata) and optional body content.

**Configuration** (`site/site.yml`):
```yaml
collections:
  articles:
    path: library/articles
    route: /blog           # Enables dynamic routes
    sort: date desc
  team:
    path: library/team
    sort: order asc
```

**Example collection item** (`library/team/sarah-chen.md`):
```markdown
---
name: Sarah Chen
role: CEO & Co-founder
avatar: https://example.com/photo.jpg
order: 1
social:
  linkedin: https://linkedin.com
---

Leading our mission to simplify web publishing.
```

Collections are processed at build time into JSON files (`public/data/team.json`), which components can fetch.

### Three Ways to Provide Structured Data

The **Team page** (`pages/team/`) demonstrates three approaches to the same component:

| Section | Approach | Best For |
|---------|----------|----------|
| Leadership | **Collection** — `data: team` | Substantial data, reusable across pages |
| Engineering | **Tagged YAML** — inline `yaml:team` block | Quick structured data, schema-validated |
| Advisors | **Markdown items** — H3 headings | Simplest approach, pure markdown |

**1. Collection fetch** (`1-leadership.md`):
```markdown
---
type: Team
data: team
---
## Leadership
```

**2. Tagged YAML block** (`2-engineering.md`):
```markdown
---
type: Team
---
## Engineering

\`\`\`yaml:team
- name: Alex Rivera
  role: Lead Engineer
  avatar: https://...
\`\`\`
```

**3. Markdown items** (`3-advisors.md`):
```markdown
---
type: Team
---
## Advisors

### Dr. Emily Watson
Strategic Advisor
Bio paragraph here.
![](photo.jpg)
[LinkedIn](https://...)
```

### Component Parameters

The same component can render differently based on parameters. The Team page also demonstrates layout variants:

| Section | Theme | Style | Columns |
|---------|-------|-------|---------|
| Leadership | `gray` | `cards` | 3 |
| Engineering | `light` | `simple` | 4 |
| Advisors | `dark` | `cards` | 2 |

Parameters are set in frontmatter and have defaults defined in `meta.js`.

### Dynamic Routes

The **Blog** uses dynamic routes to generate pages from collection data:

```
pages/blog/
├── page.yml           # fetch: /data/articles.json
├── 1-list.md          # BlogList component
└── [slug]/            # Dynamic segment
    └── 1-article.md   # Article component
```

The `[slug]` folder creates one page per article. Each article page receives:
- `content.data.article` — the current item
- `content.data.articles` — all items (for related posts)

